310 static Module::ModFlagBehavior ----
311 map_to_llvmModFlagBehavior(LLVMModuleFlagBehavior Behavior) { 0
312 switch (Behavior) { 0
313 case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorError: 0
314 return Module::ModFlagBehavior::Error; 0
315 case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorWarning: 0
316 return Module::ModFlagBehavior::Warning; 0
317 case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorRequire: 0
318 return Module::ModFlagBehavior::Require; 0
319 case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorOverride: 0
320 return Module::ModFlagBehavior::Override; 0
321 case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorAppend: 0
322 return Module::ModFlagBehavior::Append; 0
323 case LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorAppendUnique: 0
324 return Module::ModFlagBehavior::AppendUnique; 0
325 } ----
326 llvm_unreachable("Unknown LLVMModuleFlagBehavior"); 0
327 } ----
328 ----
329 static LLVMModuleFlagBehavior ----
330 map_from_llvmModFlagBehavior(Module::ModFlagBehavior Behavior) { 0
331 switch (Behavior) { 0
332 case Module::ModFlagBehavior::Error: 0
333 return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorError; 0
334 case Module::ModFlagBehavior::Warning: 0
335 return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorWarning; 0
336 case Module::ModFlagBehavior::Require: 0
337 return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorRequire; 0
338 case Module::ModFlagBehavior::Override: 0
339 return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorOverride; 0
340 case Module::ModFlagBehavior::Append: 0
341 return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorAppend; 0
342 case Module::ModFlagBehavior::AppendUnique: 0
343 return LLVMModuleFlagBehaviorAppendUnique; 0
344 default: 0
345 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled Flag Behavior"); 0
346 } ----
347 } ----

349 LLVMModuleFlagEntry *LLVMCopyModuleFlagsMetadata(LLVMModuleRef M, size_t *Len) { 0
350 SmallVector MFEs; 0
351 unwrap(M)->getModuleFlagsMetadata(MFEs); 0
352 ----
353 LLVMOpaqueModuleFlagEntry *Result = static_cast( ----
354 safe_malloc(MFEs.size() * sizeof(LLVMOpaqueModuleFlagEntry))); 0
355 for (unsigned i = 0; i < MFEs.size(); ++i) { 0
356 const auto &ModuleFlag = MFEs[i]; 0
357 Result[i].Behavior = map_from_llvmModFlagBehavior(ModuleFlag.Behavior); 0
358 Result[i].Key = ModuleFlag.Key->getString().data(); 0
359 Result[i].KeyLen = ModuleFlag.Key->getString().size(); 0
360 Result[i].Metadata = wrap(ModuleFlag.Val); 0
361 } ----
362 *Len = MFEs.size(); 0
363 return Result; 0
364 } 0

412 LLVMBool LLVMPrintModuleToFile(LLVMModuleRef M, const char *Filename, 0
413 char **ErrorMessage) { ----
414 std::error_code EC; 0
415 raw_fd_ostream dest(Filename, EC, sys::fs::OF_TextWithCRLF); 0
416 if (EC) { 0
417 *ErrorMessage = strdup(EC.message().c_str()); 0
418 return true; 0
419 } ----
420 ----
421 unwrap(M)->print(dest, nullptr); 0
422 ----
423 dest.close(); 0
424 ----
425 if (dest.has_error()) { 0
426 std::string E = "Error printing to file: " + dest.error().message(); 0
427 *ErrorMessage = strdup(E.c_str()); 0
428 return true; 0
429 } 0
430 ----
431 return false; 0
432 } 0

936 LLVMValueRef LLVMGetMetadata(LLVMValueRef Inst, unsigned KindID) { 0
937 auto *I = unwrap(Inst); 0
938 assert(I && "Expected instruction"); 0
939 if (auto *MD = I->getMetadata(KindID)) 0
940 return wrap(MetadataAsValue::get(I->getContext(), MD)); 0
941 return nullptr; 0
942 } ----
943 ----
944 // MetadataAsValue uses a canonical format which strips the actual MDNode for ----
945 // MDNode with just a single constant value, storing just a ConstantAsMetadata ----
946 // This undoes this canonicalization, reconstructing the MDNode. ----
947 static MDNode *extractMDNode(MetadataAsValue *MAV) { 0
948 Metadata *MD = MAV->getMetadata(); 0
949 assert((isa(MD) || isa(MD)) && 0
950 "Expected a metadata node or a canonicalized constant"); ----
951 ----
952 if (MDNode *N = dyn_cast(MD)) 0
953 return N; 0
954 ----
955 return MDNode::get(MAV->getContext(), MD); 0
956 } ----
957 ----
958 void LLVMSetMetadata(LLVMValueRef Inst, unsigned KindID, LLVMValueRef Val) { 0
959 MDNode *N = Val ? extractMDNode(unwrap(Val)) : nullptr; 0
960 ----
961 unwrap(Inst)->setMetadata(KindID, N); 0
962 } 0
963 ----
964 struct LLVMOpaqueValueMetadataEntry { ----
965 unsigned Kind; ----
966 LLVMMetadataRef Metadata; ----
967 }; ----
968 ----
969 using MetadataEntries = SmallVectorImpl>; ----
970 static LLVMValueMetadataEntry * ----
971 llvm_getMetadata(size_t *NumEntries, 0
972 llvm::function_ref AccessMD) { ----
973 SmallVector, 8> MVEs; 0
974 AccessMD(MVEs); 0
975 ----
976 LLVMOpaqueValueMetadataEntry *Result = ----
977 static_cast( ----
978 safe_malloc(MVEs.size() * sizeof(LLVMOpaqueValueMetadataEntry))); 0
979 for (unsigned i = 0; i < MVEs.size(); ++i) { 0
980 const auto &ModuleFlag = MVEs[i]; 0
981 Result[i].Kind = ModuleFlag.first; 0
982 Result[i].Metadata = wrap(ModuleFlag.second); 0
983 } ----
984 *NumEntries = MVEs.size(); 0
985 return Result; 0
986 } 0
987 ----
988 LLVMValueMetadataEntry * ----
989 LLVMInstructionGetAllMetadataOtherThanDebugLoc(LLVMValueRef Value, 0
990 size_t *NumEntries) { ----
991 return llvm_getMetadata(NumEntries, [&Value](MetadataEntries &Entries) { 0
992 Entries.clear(); 0
993 unwrap(Value)->getAllMetadata(Entries); 0
994 }); 0
995 } ----

1054 static LLVMValueRef getMDNodeOperandImpl(LLVMContext &Context, const MDNode *N, 0
1055 unsigned Index) { ----
1056 Metadata *Op = N->getOperand(Index); 0
1057 if (!Op) 0
1058 return nullptr; 0
1059 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(Op)) 0
1060 return wrap(C->getValue()); 0
1061 return wrap(MetadataAsValue::get(Context, Op)); 0
1062 } ----
1063 ----
1064 LLVMValueRef LLVMGetOperand(LLVMValueRef Val, unsigned Index) { 0
1065 Value *V = unwrap(Val); 0
1066 if (auto *MD = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
1067 if (auto *L = dyn_cast(MD->getMetadata())) { 0
1068 assert(Index == 0 && "Function-local metadata can only have one operand"); 0
1069 return wrap(L->getValue()); 0
1070 } ----
1071 return getMDNodeOperandImpl(V->getContext(), 0
1072 cast(MD->getMetadata()), Index); 0
1073 } ----
1074 ----
1075 return wrap(cast(V)->getOperand(Index)); 0
1076 } ----
1077 ----
1078 LLVMUseRef LLVMGetOperandUse(LLVMValueRef Val, unsigned Index) { 0
1079 Value *V = unwrap(Val); 0
1080 return wrap(&cast(V)->getOperandUse(Index)); 0
1081 } ----

1085 } 0

1093 } ----

1157 ----
1158 LLVMValueRef LLVMMDNodeInContext(LLVMContextRef C, LLVMValueRef *Vals, 0
1159 unsigned Count) { ----
1160 LLVMContext &Context = *unwrap(C); 0
1161 SmallVector MDs; 0
1162 for (auto *OV : ArrayRef(Vals, Count)) { 0
1163 Value *V = unwrap(OV); 0
1164 Metadata *MD; ----
1165 if (!V) 0
1166 MD = nullptr; 0
1167 else if (auto *C = dyn_cast(V)) 0
1168 MD = ConstantAsMetadata::get(C); 0
1169 else if (auto *MDV = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
1170 MD = MDV->getMetadata(); 0
1171 assert(!isa(MD) && "Unexpected function-local metadata " 0
1172 "outside of direct argument to call"); ----
1173 } else { ----
1174 // This is function-local metadata. Pretend to make an MDNode. ----
1175 assert(Count == 1 && 0
1176 "Expected only one operand to function-local metadata"); ----
1177 return wrap(MetadataAsValue::get(Context, LocalAsMetadata::get(V))); 0
1178 } ----
1179 ----
1180 MDs.push_back(MD); 0
1181 } ----
1182 return wrap(MetadataAsValue::get(Context, MDNode::get(Context, MDs))); 0
1183 } 0
1184 ----
1185 LLVMValueRef LLVMMDNode(LLVMValueRef *Vals, unsigned Count) { 0
1186 return LLVMMDNodeInContext(LLVMGetGlobalContext(), Vals, Count); 0
1187 } ----
1188 ----
1189 LLVMValueRef LLVMMetadataAsValue(LLVMContextRef C, LLVMMetadataRef MD) { 0
1190 return wrap(MetadataAsValue::get(*unwrap(C), unwrap(MD))); 0
1191 } ----
1192 ----
1193 LLVMMetadataRef LLVMValueAsMetadata(LLVMValueRef Val) { 0
1194 auto *V = unwrap(Val); 0
1195 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(V)) 0
1196 return wrap(ConstantAsMetadata::get(C)); 0
1197 if (auto *MAV = dyn_cast(V)) 0
1198 return wrap(MAV->getMetadata()); 0
1199 return wrap(ValueAsMetadata::get(V)); 0
1200 } ----
1201 ----
1202 const char *LLVMGetMDString(LLVMValueRef V, unsigned *Length) { 0
1203 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast(unwrap(V))) 0
1204 if (const MDString *S = dyn_cast(MD->getMetadata())) { 0
1205 *Length = S->getString().size(); 0
1206 return S->getString().data(); 0
1207 } ----
1208 *Length = 0; 0
1209 return nullptr; 0
1210 } ----

1261 const char *LLVMGetNamedMetadataName(LLVMNamedMDNodeRef NMD, size_t *NameLen) { 0

1263 *NameLen = NamedNode->getName().size(); 0
1264 return NamedNode->getName().data(); 0
1265 } ----
1266 ----
1267 void LLVMGetMDNodeOperands(LLVMValueRef V, LLVMValueRef *Dest) { 0
1268 auto *MD = unwrap(V); 0
1269 if (auto *MDV = dyn_cast(MD->getMetadata())) { 0
1270 *Dest = wrap(MDV->getValue()); 0
1271 return; 0
1272 } ----
1273 const auto *N = cast(MD->getMetadata()); 0
1274 const unsigned numOperands = N->getNumOperands(); 0
1275 LLVMContext &Context = unwrap(V)->getContext(); 0
1276 for (unsigned i = 0; i < numOperands; i++) 0
1277 Dest[i] = getMDNodeOperandImpl(Context, N, i); 0
1278 } ----
1279 ----
1280 void LLVMReplaceMDNodeOperandWith(LLVMValueRef V, unsigned Index, 0
1281 LLVMMetadataRef Replacement) { ----
1282 auto *MD = cast(unwrap(V)); 0
1283 auto *N = cast(MD->getMetadata()); 0
1284 N->replaceOperandWith(Index, unwrap(Replacement)); 0
1285 } 0
1286 ----
1287 unsigned LLVMGetNamedMetadataNumOperands(LLVMModuleRef M, const char *Name) { 0
1288 if (NamedMDNode *N = unwrap(M)->getNamedMetadata(Name)) { 0
1289 return N->getNumOperands(); 0
1290 } ----
1291 return 0; 0
1292 } ----
1293 ----
1294 void LLVMGetNamedMetadataOperands(LLVMModuleRef M, const char *Name, 0
1295 LLVMValueRef *Dest) { ----
1296 NamedMDNode *N = unwrap(M)->getNamedMetadata(Name); 0
1297 if (!N) 0
1298 return; 0
1299 LLVMContext &Context = unwrap(M)->getContext(); 0
1300 for (unsigned i=0;igetNumOperands();i++) 0
1301 Dest[i] = wrap(MetadataAsValue::get(Context, N->getOperand(i))); 0
1302 } ----
1303 ----
1304 void LLVMAddNamedMetadataOperand(LLVMModuleRef M, const char *Name, 0
1305 LLVMValueRef Val) { ----
1306 NamedMDNode *N = unwrap(M)->getOrInsertNamedMetadata(Name); 0
1307 if (!N) 0
1308 return; 0
1309 if (!Val) 0
1310 return; 0
1311 N->addOperand(extractMDNode(unwrap(Val))); 0
1312 } ----
1313 ----
1314 const char *LLVMGetDebugLocDirectory(LLVMValueRef Val, unsigned *Length) { 0
1315 if (!Length) return nullptr; 0
1316 StringRef S; 0
1317 if (const auto *I = dyn_cast(unwrap(Val))) { 0
1318 if (const auto &DL = I->getDebugLoc()) { 0
1319 S = DL->getDirectory(); 0
1320 } ----
1321 } else if (const auto *GV = dyn_cast(unwrap(Val))) { 0
1322 SmallVector GVEs; 0
1323 GV->getDebugInfo(GVEs); 0
1324 if (GVEs.size()) 0
1325 if (const DIGlobalVariable *DGV = GVEs[0]->getVariable()) 0
1326 S = DGV->getDirectory(); 0
1327 } else if (const auto *F = dyn_cast(unwrap(Val))) { 0
1328 if (const DISubprogram *DSP = F->getSubprogram()) 0
1329 S = DSP->getDirectory(); 0
1330 } else { ----
1331 assert(0 && "Expected Instruction, GlobalVariable or Function"); 0
1332 return nullptr; ----
1333 } ----
1334 *Length = S.size(); 0
1335 return S.data(); 0
1336 } ----
1337 ----
1338 const char *LLVMGetDebugLocFilename(LLVMValueRef Val, unsigned *Length) { 0
1339 if (!Length) return nullptr; 0
1340 StringRef S; 0
1341 if (const auto *I = dyn_cast(unwrap(Val))) { 0
1342 if (const auto &DL = I->getDebugLoc()) { 0
1343 S = DL->getFilename(); 0
1344 } ----
1345 } else if (const auto *GV = dyn_cast(unwrap(Val))) { 0
1346 SmallVector GVEs; 0
1347 GV->getDebugInfo(GVEs); 0
1348 if (GVEs.size()) 0
1349 if (const DIGlobalVariable *DGV = GVEs[0]->getVariable()) 0
1350 S = DGV->getFilename(); 0
1351 } else if (const auto *F = dyn_cast(unwrap(Val))) { 0
1352 if (const DISubprogram *DSP = F->getSubprogram()) 0
1353 S = DSP->getFilename(); 0
1354 } else { ----
1355 assert(0 && "Expected Instruction, GlobalVariable or Function"); 0
1356 return nullptr; ----
1357 } ----
1358 *Length = S.size(); 0
1359 return S.data(); 0
1360 } ----
1361 ----
1362 unsigned LLVMGetDebugLocLine(LLVMValueRef Val) { 0

1364 if (const auto *I = dyn_cast(unwrap(Val))) { 0
1365 if (const auto &DL = I->getDebugLoc()) { 0
1366 L = DL->getLine(); 0
1367 } ----
1368 } else if (const auto *GV = dyn_cast(unwrap(Val))) { 0
1369 SmallVector GVEs; 0
1370 GV->getDebugInfo(GVEs); 0
1371 if (GVEs.size()) 0
1372 if (const DIGlobalVariable *DGV = GVEs[0]->getVariable()) 0
1373 L = DGV->getLine(); 0
1374 } else if (const auto *F = dyn_cast(unwrap(Val))) { 0
1375 if (const DISubprogram *DSP = F->getSubprogram()) 0
1376 L = DSP->getLine(); 0
1377 } else { ----
1378 assert(0 && "Expected Instruction, GlobalVariable or Function"); 0
1379 return -1; ----
1380 } ----
1381 return L; 0
1382 } ----

1440 double LLVMConstRealGetDouble(LLVMValueRef ConstantVal, LLVMBool *LosesInfo) { 0
1441 ConstantFP *cFP = unwrap(ConstantVal) ; 0
1442 Type *Ty = cFP->getType(); 0
1443 ----
1444 if (Ty->isHalfTy() || Ty->isBFloatTy() || Ty->isFloatTy() || 0
1445 Ty->isDoubleTy()) { 0
1446 *LosesInfo = false; 0
1447 return cFP->getValueAPF().convertToDouble(); 0
1448 } ----
1449 ----
1450 bool APFLosesInfo; ----
1451 APFloat APF = cFP->getValueAPF(); 0
1452 APF.convert(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &APFLosesInfo); 0
1453 *LosesInfo = APFLosesInfo; 0
1454 return APF.convertToDouble(); 0
1455 } 0

1532 /*-- Opcode mapping */ ----
1533 ----
1534 static LLVMOpcode map_to_llvmopcode(int opcode) 0
1535 { ----
1536 switch (opcode) { 0
1537 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled Opcode."); 0
1538 #define HANDLE_INST(num, opc, clas) case num: return LLVM##opc; ----
1539 #include "llvm/IR/Instruction.def" ----
1540 #undef HANDLE_INST ----
1541 } ----
1542 } ----
1543 ----
1544 static int map_from_llvmopcode(LLVMOpcode code) 0
1545 { ----
1546 switch (code) { 0
1547 #define HANDLE_INST(num, opc, clas) case LLVM##opc: return num; ----
1548 #include "llvm/IR/Instruction.def" ----
1549 #undef HANDLE_INST ----
1550 } ----
1551 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled Opcode."); 0
1552 } ----

1844 LLVMLinkage LLVMGetLinkage(LLVMValueRef Global) { 0
1845 switch (unwrap(Global)->getLinkage()) { 0
1846 case GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage: 0
1847 return LLVMExternalLinkage; 0
1848 case GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage: 0
1849 return LLVMAvailableExternallyLinkage; 0
1850 case GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage: 0
1851 return LLVMLinkOnceAnyLinkage; 0
1852 case GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage: 0
1853 return LLVMLinkOnceODRLinkage; 0
1854 case GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage: 0
1855 return LLVMWeakAnyLinkage; 0
1856 case GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage: 0
1857 return LLVMWeakODRLinkage; 0
1858 case GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage: 0
1859 return LLVMAppendingLinkage; 0
1860 case GlobalValue::InternalLinkage: 0
1861 return LLVMInternalLinkage; 0
1862 case GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage: 0
1863 return LLVMPrivateLinkage; 0
1864 case GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage: 0
1865 return LLVMExternalWeakLinkage; 0
1866 case GlobalValue::CommonLinkage: 0
1867 return LLVMCommonLinkage; 0
1868 } ----
1869 ----
1870 llvm_unreachable("Invalid GlobalValue linkage!"); 0
1871 } ----
1872 ----
1873 void LLVMSetLinkage(LLVMValueRef Global, LLVMLinkage Linkage) { 0
1874 GlobalValue *GV = unwrap(Global); 0
1875 ----
1876 switch (Linkage) { 0
1877 case LLVMExternalLinkage: 0
1878 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage); 0
1879 break; 0
1880 case LLVMAvailableExternallyLinkage: 0
1881 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage); 0
1882 break; 0
1883 case LLVMLinkOnceAnyLinkage: 0
1884 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage); 0
1885 break; 0
1886 case LLVMLinkOnceODRLinkage: 0
1887 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage); 0
1888 break; 0
1889 case LLVMLinkOnceODRAutoHideLinkage: 0
1890 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1891 errs() << "LLVMSetLinkage(): LLVMLinkOnceODRAutoHideLinkage is no " ----
1892 "longer supported."); ----
1893 break; 0
1894 case LLVMWeakAnyLinkage: 0
1895 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage); 0
1896 break; 0
1897 case LLVMWeakODRLinkage: 0
1898 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage); 0
1899 break; 0
1900 case LLVMAppendingLinkage: 0
1901 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage); 0
1902 break; 0
1903 case LLVMInternalLinkage: 0
1904 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::InternalLinkage); 0
1905 break; 0
1906 case LLVMPrivateLinkage: 0
1907 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage); 0
1908 break; 0
1909 case LLVMLinkerPrivateLinkage: 0
1910 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage); 0
1911 break; 0
1912 case LLVMLinkerPrivateWeakLinkage: 0
1913 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage); 0
1914 break; 0
1915 case LLVMDLLImportLinkage: 0
1916 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1917 errs() ----
1918 << "LLVMSetLinkage(): LLVMDLLImportLinkage is no longer supported."); ----
1919 break; 0
1920 case LLVMDLLExportLinkage: 0
1921 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1922 errs() ----
1923 << "LLVMSetLinkage(): LLVMDLLExportLinkage is no longer supported."); ----
1924 break; 0
1925 case LLVMExternalWeakLinkage: 0
1926 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage); 0
1927 break; 0
1928 case LLVMGhostLinkage: 0
1929 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1930 errs() << "LLVMSetLinkage(): LLVMGhostLinkage is no longer supported."); ----
1931 break; 0
1932 case LLVMCommonLinkage: 0
1933 GV->setLinkage(GlobalValue::CommonLinkage); 0
1934 break; 0
1935 } ----
1936 } 0

2007 /*--.. Operations on global variables, load and store instructions .........--*/ ----
2008 ----
2009 unsigned LLVMGetAlignment(LLVMValueRef V) { 0
2010 Value *P = unwrap(V); 0
2011 if (GlobalObject *GV = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2012 return GV->getAlign() ? GV->getAlign()->value() : 0; 0
2013 if (AllocaInst *AI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2014 return AI->getAlign().value(); 0
2015 if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2016 return LI->getAlign().value(); 0
2017 if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2018 return SI->getAlign().value(); 0
2019 if (AtomicRMWInst *RMWI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2020 return RMWI->getAlign().value(); 0
2021 if (AtomicCmpXchgInst *CXI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2022 return CXI->getAlign().value(); 0
2023 ----
2024 llvm_unreachable( 0
2025 "only GlobalValue, AllocaInst, LoadInst, StoreInst, AtomicRMWInst, " ----
2026 "and AtomicCmpXchgInst have alignment"); ----
2027 } ----
2028 ----
2029 void LLVMSetAlignment(LLVMValueRef V, unsigned Bytes) { 0
2030 Value *P = unwrap(V); 0
2031 if (GlobalObject *GV = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2032 GV->setAlignment(MaybeAlign(Bytes)); 0
2033 else if (AllocaInst *AI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2034 AI->setAlignment(Align(Bytes)); 0
2035 else if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2036 LI->setAlignment(Align(Bytes)); 0
2037 else if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2038 SI->setAlignment(Align(Bytes)); 0
2039 else if (AtomicRMWInst *RMWI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2040 RMWI->setAlignment(Align(Bytes)); 0
2041 else if (AtomicCmpXchgInst *CXI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
2042 CXI->setAlignment(Align(Bytes)); 0
2043 else ----
2044 llvm_unreachable( 0
2045 "only GlobalValue, AllocaInst, LoadInst, StoreInst, AtomicRMWInst, and " ----
2046 "and AtomicCmpXchgInst have alignment"); ----
2047 } 0

2054 Instr->getAllMetadata(Entries); 0
2055 } else { ----
2056 unwrap(Value)->getAllMetadata(Entries); 0
2057 } ----
2058 }); 0
2059 } ----

3040 auto I = Instr ? unwrap(Instr)->getIterator() : BB->end(); 0
3041 unwrap(Builder)->SetInsertPoint(BB, I); 0
3042 } 0
3043 ----
3044 void LLVMPositionBuilderBefore(LLVMBuilderRef Builder, LLVMValueRef Instr) { 0
3045 Instruction *I = unwrap(Instr); 0
3046 unwrap(Builder)->SetInsertPoint(I->getParent(), I->getIterator()); 0
3047 } 0
3048 ----

3050 BasicBlock *BB = unwrap(Block); 0
3051 unwrap(Builder)->SetInsertPoint(BB); 0
3052 } 0

3478 ----
3479 LLVMValueRef LLVMBuildMalloc(LLVMBuilderRef B, LLVMTypeRef Ty, 0
3480 const char *Name) { ----
3481 Type* ITy = Type::getInt32Ty(unwrap(B)->GetInsertBlock()->getContext()); 0
3482 Constant* AllocSize = ConstantExpr::getSizeOf(unwrap(Ty)); 0
3483 AllocSize = ConstantExpr::getTruncOrBitCast(AllocSize, ITy); 0
3484 Instruction* Malloc = CallInst::CreateMalloc(unwrap(B)->GetInsertBlock(), 0
3485 ITy, unwrap(Ty), AllocSize, ----
3486 nullptr, nullptr, ""); ----
3487 return wrap(unwrap(B)->Insert(Malloc, Twine(Name))); 0
3488 } ----
3489 ----
3490 LLVMValueRef LLVMBuildArrayMalloc(LLVMBuilderRef B, LLVMTypeRef Ty, 0
3491 LLVMValueRef Val, const char *Name) { ----
3492 Type* ITy = Type::getInt32Ty(unwrap(B)->GetInsertBlock()->getContext()); 0
3493 Constant* AllocSize = ConstantExpr::getSizeOf(unwrap(Ty)); 0
3494 AllocSize = ConstantExpr::getTruncOrBitCast(AllocSize, ITy); 0
3495 Instruction* Malloc = CallInst::CreateMalloc(unwrap(B)->GetInsertBlock(), 0
3496 ITy, unwrap(Ty), AllocSize, ----
3497 unwrap(Val), nullptr, ""); ----
3498 return wrap(unwrap(B)->Insert(Malloc, Twine(Name))); 0
3499 } ----

3551 static AtomicOrdering mapFromLLVMOrdering(LLVMAtomicOrdering Ordering) { 0
3552 switch (Ordering) { 0
3553 case LLVMAtomicOrderingNotAtomic: return AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic; 0
3554 case LLVMAtomicOrderingUnordered: return AtomicOrdering::Unordered; 0
3555 case LLVMAtomicOrderingMonotonic: return AtomicOrdering::Monotonic; 0
3556 case LLVMAtomicOrderingAcquire: return AtomicOrdering::Acquire; 0
3557 case LLVMAtomicOrderingRelease: return AtomicOrdering::Release; 0
3558 case LLVMAtomicOrderingAcquireRelease: 0
3559 return AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease; 0
3560 case LLVMAtomicOrderingSequentiallyConsistent: 0
3561 return AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent; 0
3562 } ----
3563 ----
3564 llvm_unreachable("Invalid LLVMAtomicOrdering value!"); 0
3565 } ----
3566 ----

3570 case AtomicOrdering::Unordered: return LLVMAtomicOrderingUnordered; 0
3571 case AtomicOrdering::Monotonic: return LLVMAtomicOrderingMonotonic; 0
3572 case AtomicOrdering::Acquire: return LLVMAtomicOrderingAcquire; 0
3573 case AtomicOrdering::Release: return LLVMAtomicOrderingRelease; 0
3574 case AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease: 0
3575 return LLVMAtomicOrderingAcquireRelease; 0
3576 case AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent: 0
3577 return LLVMAtomicOrderingSequentiallyConsistent; 0
3578 } ----

3580 llvm_unreachable("Invalid AtomicOrdering value!"); 0
3581 } ----

3593 case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpMin: return AtomicRMWInst::Min; 0

3598 case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpFMax: return AtomicRMWInst::FMax; 0
3599 case LLVMAtomicRMWBinOpFMin: return AtomicRMWInst::FMin; 0

3671 LLVMBool LLVMGetVolatile(LLVMValueRef MemAccessInst) { 0
3672 Value *P = unwrap(MemAccessInst); 0
3673 if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
3674 return LI->isVolatile(); 0
3675 if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
3676 return SI->isVolatile(); 0
3677 if (AtomicRMWInst *AI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
3678 return AI->isVolatile(); 0
3679 return cast(P)->isVolatile(); 0
3680 } ----
3681 ----
3682 void LLVMSetVolatile(LLVMValueRef MemAccessInst, LLVMBool isVolatile) { 0
3683 Value *P = unwrap(MemAccessInst); 0
3684 if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
3685 return LI->setVolatile(isVolatile); 0
3686 if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
3687 return SI->setVolatile(isVolatile); 0
3688 if (AtomicRMWInst *AI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
3689 return AI->setVolatile(isVolatile); 0
3690 return cast(P)->setVolatile(isVolatile); 0
3691 } ----

3701 LLVMAtomicOrdering LLVMGetOrdering(LLVMValueRef MemAccessInst) { 0
3702 Value *P = unwrap(MemAccessInst); 0
3703 AtomicOrdering O; ----
3704 if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
3705 O = LI->getOrdering(); 0
3706 else if (StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
3707 O = SI->getOrdering(); 0
3708 else ----
3709 O = cast(P)->getOrdering(); 0
3710 return mapToLLVMOrdering(O); 0
3711 } ----
3712 ----
3713 void LLVMSetOrdering(LLVMValueRef MemAccessInst, LLVMAtomicOrdering Ordering) { 0
3714 Value *P = unwrap(MemAccessInst); 0
3715 AtomicOrdering O = mapFromLLVMOrdering(Ordering); 0
3716 ----
3717 if (LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast(P)) 0
3718 return LI->setOrdering(O); 0
3719 return cast(P)->setOrdering(O); 0
3720 } ----
